	<h3>Related Documents</h3>      
	<ul>
	
	<li><a href="/en/birth_family_relationships/separation_and_divorce/sep_divorce_pensions.html">How pensions are assessed during a
  separation/divorce/dissolution</a><br>Courts in Ireland have the power to treat pensions as assets. How pensions are divided and explanation of pension adjustment orders.</li>
	
	<li><a href="/en/birth_family_relationships/separation_and_divorce/divorce_decrees.html">Divorce decrees</a><br>A divorce decree allows both parties to a marriage to remarry. Special conditions must be met, however, before a court can grant a divorce.</li>
	
	<li><a href="/en/birth_family_relationships/separation_and_divorce/judicial_separation.html">Judicial separation</a><br>Applications for a judicial separation in Ireland are made to the court.  Find out what a judicial separation means, how to apply for it and how it works.</li>
	
	</ul>	
